le=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">13.56 &#x000b1; 4.80</td><td style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.05</td></tr><tr><td style=" color:#221E1F;" align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Day 5 APACHE II</td><td style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">18.14 &#x000b1; 5.91</td><td style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">15.13 &#x000b1; 4.70</td><td style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.23</td></tr></tbody></table></table-wrap><p>The mean concentrations of midazolam in sampling times followed by two methods are shown in <xref ref-type="table" rid="T2">Table 2</xref> and the time-concentration curve of each method is shown in <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F1">Figures 1</xref> and <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">2</xref>.</p><table-wrap id="T2" position="float"><label>Table 2</label><caption><p>The mean concentrations of Midazolam (ng/mL) in sampling times following two methods.</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><th style=" color:#221E1F;" align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
